        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "The Romanovitch family had long served the hoary monsters known as the Tzimisce. Your family in particular was promised to one voivode, a Tzimisce who held lands and territory in the Ukraine, and who had a whole clan of your revenant family in a village nearby, bound to him in service. Escape was unthinkable to the likes of all of you. You worked and served your masters, useful for your strength and you ability to protect, but not much else. This all changed, however, when Napolean and his armies invaded Russia, bringing with them a host of outside vampires; the rabble that was the Brujah, the bootlicking Ventrue, and worst of all, the usurping Tremere. Your sire had long spoken of the Tremere, often with a curse, for all knew the story of how they had stolen their birthright. You perhaps would have known no differently, if it weren't for the raid on your family manse at the hands of a long lost revenant family, the Ducheskis, who had defected with the Tremere long ago. They were interested in new genetics and weakening your master, and you found yourself willingly going along with them, offering your services to the Tremere in exchange for your knowledge of the Tzimisce and your own kin. They gladly took up your offer, requesting only that you offer your own seed to father a Ducheski child, and afterwards, accept the Tremere embrace. It was your information that led the Tremere chantry of Moscow to defeat your former master, and led you down the path of of a Sabbat"
        ],
